choices.text:
what are the catagories of figures of speech?
There are several categories of figures of speech, including:1. Simile and metaphor2. Personification3. Hyperbole4. Alliteration5. Onomatopoeia6. Idiom7. Irony8. Pun9. Paradox10. OxymoronEach category has its own unique way of expressing ideas or conveying meaning through the use of words, phrases, or images that are not meant to be taken literally.
